Carlyle May Invest $1 Billion in Brazil Over 2 Years, Folha Says

-- B y   A d r i a n a   B r a s i l e i r o
-- 
2011-05-15T13:41:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-15/carlyle-may-invest-1-billion-in-brazil-over-2-years-folha-says.html
The  Carlyle Group  plans to invest $1
billion in  Brazil  over the next two years,  Folha de S. Paulo 
reported, citing Juan Carlos Felix, a director at the private
equity fund.  Carlyle plans to buy stakes in companies involved in
retail, infrastructure and logistics, the newspaper said, citing
Felix.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adriana Brasileiro in  Rio de Janeiro  at 
